{{Infobox television | show_name = Religion & Ethics Newsweekly | image = <!-- include ALT text per [[MOS:ALT]] guideline --> | caption = | show_name_2 = | genre = Ethics, religious and spirituality news | creator = | developer = | writer = | director = | creative_director = | presenter = [[Bob Abernethy]] | starring = | judges = | voices = | narrated = | theme_music_composer = | opentheme = | endtheme = | composer = | country = [[United States]] | language = English | num_seasons = <!-- or num_series --> | num_episodes = | list_episodes = | executive_producer = | producer = [[WNET|Thirteen/WNET]] | editor = | location = [[Washington, D.C.]] | cinematography = | camera = | runtime = 30 minutes | company = | distributor = | channel = [[Public Broadcasting Service|PBS]]<!-- or network --> | picture_format = | audio_format = | first_run = | first_aired = October 3, 1997 | last_aired = February 24, 2017 | preceded_by = | followed_by = | related = | website = https://www.pbs.org/wnet/religionandethics | production_website = }}
'''''Religion & Ethics Newsweekly''''' was an [[United States|American]] weekly television [[news magazine|news-magazine]] program which aired on [[Public Broadcasting Service|PBS]].
==History and content== Premiering in 1997, Religion & Ethics Newsweekly was devoted to the news of [[religion]] and [[spirituality]], along with major [[ethical]] issues. The program explored the top [[moral questions]] facing the country and profiles notable people and groups in the world of religion and ethics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/wnet/religionandethics/about-the-series/ |title=About the Series &#124; Religion & Ethics NewsWeekly |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website=Pbs.org |publisher=[[PBS]] |accessdate=August 23, 2016 |quote=}}</ref> As of February, 2017 the series has been cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|title=Religion & Ethics NewsWeekly Cancelled After 20-Year Run|url=http://renewcanceltv.com/religion-ethics-newsweekly-cancelled-20-year-run/|website=RenewCanceltV|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref>
==Production and distribution== It had been produced by [[WNET|Thirteen/WNET]] in [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], since its premiere, and was filmed on location worldwide. The main studio was in downtown [[Washington, D.C.]], in the same building as [[Reuters]] [[news agency]].
The program was distributed to PBS stations nationwide.
==Host== The program was hosted by journalist [[Bob Abernethy]].
